      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p>The papers of Samuel Hay Kauffmann (1829-1906) span the years
		  1871-1896 and pertain primarily to his research on equestrian statues. Items
		  include correspondence, research notes, printed matter, and drafts of a paper
		  on the subject that Kauffmann delivered before the Literary Society of
		  Washington. Correspondents include Joseph Alexis Bailly, Truman Howe Bartlett,
		  Benj French &amp; Co., and Joesph Edgar Boehm.</p>
      </scopecontent>
